In direct reply to the questions raised. Long story short. You need a compatible DVD burner for "proper" (meaning CIV like Forza 4 won't notice anything) XGD3 burning. Consider it an investment of 20-25 bucks, and you'll be "okay," just like before. If you're anyway looking for a new burner, just buy one of the compatible models, they'll do XGD3 as well as anything else a burner usually does.

Flashing of the custom firmware for that burner is straight-forward, if you flashed before, you will have no problems. No need to open your console for this, etc. Really no big deal. Good luck!

